rComments: As I'm nearing my final (extra) semester I feel it necessary to warn newcoming students as well as students in their later years of Anthro. Beware: Prof Kurtovic actually cares about the content she is teaching and if you let her, she will be the best professor you've ever had. Be prepared to actually learn something. Be prepared to be challenged.

Prof Kurtovic is one of the best profs I've ever had, she really cares about her students and checks in on them outside of class (one time I emailed her at 3 am and she set up a zoom meeting to check on my mental health). She teaches extremely well and makes everyone interested in the class. Readings are easy to understand and she is very fun!

This was my first ever class with professor Kurtovic and she was absolutely fantastic. She is so passionate about what she teaches, and you can tell. What's great is that professor Kurtovic can SHARE that passion with her students. It makes the material very interesting and fun to learn. If I could, I would definitely take another class with her!!

Professor Kurtovic is someone who is a natural teacher and mentor. I have had her for various courses, and they have been my favorite throughout my degree. She makes sure we learn everything we need, the readings, course materials and testing is all in a perfect fit and flow. She always goes out of her way for her students! Must take
Caring, inspiring and truly defies the conventional. There are a lot of readings and discussions so be prepared!

Dont take her class under the precept that its a fun and chill elective. Unless youre willing to put in work, this is not the class for you. (That doesnt make her a bad prof, just a warning for those thinking itll be an easy ride).

One of the best professors I've had. Readings were posted on brightspace including an online source to the ethnographic book we needed for the final. Fair grader, lots of feedback. One assignment, one in-class midterm & take-home final (no mind tricks, all topics discussed in readings and in class). 100% recommend taking this class and others w her

She's very straight-forward about what she wants. She wants you to do the readings so you automatically get 100% if you can prove you did the readings and not just read the powerpoints for the midterm. 10% of the grade is based on attendance. The final was straight forward and short. Easy marker for sure!
